---
title: Buffalo Chicken Tacos with Melty Cheddar & a Creamy Ranch Celery Slaw
description: What if we told you there was a way you could get all the tangy-spicy-creamy-crunchy goodness of Buffalo chicken, ranch, and veggie dippers—minus the messy eating experience? Well, friends, our chefs have dreamed up just that. They season chicken breast strips with Frank’s Red Hot seasoning, then sauté with scallions and stuff into warm tortillas layered with melty cheddar. Of course, they didn’t forget about the ranch and veggie combo—they turned it into a creamy, ranch-dressed slaw for topping the tacos. This is the Buffalo experience we’ve been waiting for!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/buffalo-chicken-tacos-4fdedf5f.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/buffalo-chicken-tacos-5f1b2cfdb47fee1c3b449187-0aa3f2ca.pdf
course: main course
author: HelloFresh
time required: 15 minutes
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 790 kcal
  fat: 44 g
  saturated fat: 16 g
  carbohydrates: 62 g
  sugar: 7 g
  protein: 40 g
  fiber: 2 g
  sodium: 1800 mg
servings: 2
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/buffalo-chicken-tacos-5f1b2cfdb47fee1c3b449187
---

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce.

Thinly slice @celery{2.5%ounce} on a diagonal. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; place in a #medium bowl{}. Toss with a drizzle of @vegetable oil{2%teaspoon}, @Frank's RedHot® Original Seasoning Blend{7.2%g}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring, until browned, ~{4-5%minutes}.

Stir in half the scallions; cook until scallions are softened and chicken is cooked through, ~{1%minute} more.

While chicken cooks, in a second medium bowl, combine @coleslaw mix{4%ounce}, celery, @sour cream{2%tablespoon}, @ranch dressing{1.5%ounce}, and remaining scallions. Season with salt and pepper.

Place @flour tortillas{6} on a #baking sheet{} in a single layer; evenly sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup}. Bake until cheese melts, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with chicken and slaw. Top with as much @?hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like and serve.